cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.CV 

The paper introduces a new off-policy algorithm for meta-Reinforcement Learning (meta-RL), which involves machine learning, artificial intelligence, and robotics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also uses context variables and multi-task objectives, which are common in control systems (cs.SY) and computer vision (cs.CV), respectively, making them less likely but still possible categories.
